<doc id="356438" wikidata="Q5201692" url="?curid=356438" title="Czartak">
<text>Czartak () was a regional literary group in Poland, founded after World War I by Emil Zegad≈Çowicz. Its most famous member was Zofia Kossak-Szczucka. Other members included Edward Kozikowski, Jan Nepomucen Miller and Janina Brzostowska.

Czartak&#x27;s program may be described as a mystical naivet√© that joined a love of nature with a disgust for modern civilization. Czartak&#x27;s writers were fascinated by expressionism.

