<doc id="356522" wikidata="Q7444342" url="?curid=356522" title="Secretary of State for Employment">
<text>The secretary of state for employment was a position in the Cabinet of the United Kingdom. In 1995, it was merged with [[secretary of state for education]] to make the secretary of state for education and employment. In 2001, the employment functions were hived off and transferred to the secretary of state for social security to form the [[secretary of state for work and pensions]].

