<doc id="356624" wikidata="Q579801" url="?curid=356624" title="Gothenburg and Bohus County">
<text>Gothenburg and Bohus County () was a county of Sweden until 1 January 1998, when it was merged with Skaraborg County and √Ñlvsborg County to form V√§stra G√∂taland County.

The county was named after the city of Gothenburg and the historical province of Bohusl√§n. Gothenburg was the seat of residence for the governor and represented the westernmost part of the province of V√§sterg√∂tland.

